  <brief_title>Double Lock Versus Continuous Non-locking Technique for Closure of Rectus Sheath in Cesarean Sections on Post-operative Pain</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Ain Shams Maternity Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Ain Shams Maternity Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this trial we compare the effect of 2 closure techniques of the rectus sheath during
      cesarean sections on postoperative pain. One closure technique is double lock technique and
      the other is the conventional continuous non-locking technique.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
